==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydrolysis
<hw>Hy*drol"y*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 1 + <ets>-lysis</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A chemical process causing the splitting of a
chemical bond by the addition of the elements of water. <as>Where the
bond which is split is not part of a ring structure, this process causes
formation of two compounds from one compound plus water, as in the
<ex>hydrolysis</ex> of the ester bonds of fats during
<stype>saponification</stype></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydrolytic</ent>⟦br⟧
